It was previously shown that thalidomide enhances TCR-mediated T cells activation by by-passing T cell need for co-stimulation by accessory molecules, such as the B7 protein together with the CD28 protein, and therefore can overcome T cell deficiency 25 .

Finally, it was also reported that thalidomide prevents NF-kB from binding to the promoters of its target genes, including TNF-alpha and IFN-Gamma thereby reducing excessive inflammatory response 27,28 .
